children.subject: Hm it could be a mistake then. Regardless you should contact the instructor and/or course staff to make sure. The instructors on this piazza usually do not deal with enrollments for specific classes.

@Nico, this is OP here. I definitely do meet the prereqs for the class, as I've taken 61c already. I also thought it could have been an issue with the discussion section I enrolled in no longer being available, but that is not the case
Recieved the same email, and same situation on CalCentral. I thought I was the only one, and so I have emailed eecs advising. When I get a response, I’ll post it here too.

When we expanded the class, I had to set up a second discussion section (at the same time as the first) because the room for the discussion was too small to accommodate everyone. As a result, I had to balance the enrollment between the two sections.

Unfortunately, the way the enrollment system works, I couldn't simply swap sections. I had to drop and re-enroll you into the new discussion section.

Sorry for any confusion/distress.

See my note above about how the enrollment system forces me to drop you & then manually re-enroll you if you are wait listed for a class and have a time conflict. I cannot simply force you in from the wait list. Unfortunately that triggers an email for each action I take.

Dropped from course for Administrative drop?

Hi,

I was recently on waitlist for CS 170 and after dropping 61C, last evening, I was added to the course some time this morning. I checked my email just now and I found this email sent at 7:30 PM: 

You have been DROPPED from the following class:

Class: COMPSCI   170 

Section: 001

Reason: Administrative drop.

I'm not sure if this email was issued before or after I was added to the course, but as of right now I am still in CS170 on Calcentral. Should I be worried about anything or can I safely assume I'm in the class?
